{"type":"message","id":"ab56721b","parentId":"6a850178","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:58:05.260Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_WL4PVCkdL45KbLMYXltuq1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — March 31, 2026\n\n## Major Build Day — Massive Feature Sprint\n\n### Sub-Agent Dispatch System (established today)\n- All 10+ agents now available for dispatch as sub-agents\n- Config updated: `subagents.allowAgents` includes all agents\n- Pattern: Lucy requests → Michael dispatches appropriate agent → agent runs autonomously → Michael relays results\n- Parallel dispatch works well (4 agents at once today)\n- **Lesson learned**: Don't manually fix things when I can dispatch Uriel. Lucy called this out.\n\n### MAGI v2 Features Built Today\n1. **WhatsApp Allowlist Manager** (Uriel) — Settings page, add/remove/label/role/access per contact\n2. **Message Forwarding Rules** (Uriel) — forward/forward_summarize/notify rules per contact\n3. **Personal Knowledge Base** (Rafael) — auto-save research, search, MAGI page at /magi2/knowledge/\n4. **Mini Roundtable** (Gabriel) — multi-agent discussion page at /magi2/roundtable/, 3 modes (on-demand, scheduled, smart trigger)\n5. **Smart Notifications** (Samael) — HEARTBEAT.md updated, cron setup docs, template responses\n6. **MAGI lama (/council) route removed** — using MAGI v2 (/magi2) only now\n\n### Paul Simulator (D&D Web App) — Full Build\n- Live at: https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/dnd\n- Guide: https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/dnd/guide.html\n- **Name**: \"Paul Simulator\" (not \"D&D 2024\", not \"Angkringan Balikpapan\")\n- **PIN-per-player auth**: DM gets 6-digit PIN, each player gets unique 4-digit PIN\n- **Features**: Character Sheet (2024 rules), 3D Dice Roller, Initiative Tracker, Spell Book, DM Party Overview, Session Notes, AI Summary, Save to Obsidian, NPC Manager + AI Generator, Monster Bestiary (50 monsters) + AI Generator, Combat Integration\n- **Known issues fixed**: RTL text reversal (use HTML dir=\"ltr\" not CSS), mobile layout overflow, dice auto-roll on select (should just select)\n- **Persistence**: localStorage for browser, JSON files server-side, auto-backup 7 days, Obsidian sync\n\n### Research Done (Metis)\n1. **Hitam Manis Cafe Balikpapan** — 10+ branches, 4.6/5, homegrown coffee chain\n2. **28 Coffee Balikpapan** — 22+ outlets nationwide, 4.7/5, owned by Platinum Hotel Group\n3. **D&D 2024 Rules Reference** — compiled manually after Metis timeout\n4. **NPC/Monster/Combat Mechanics** — research for Paul Simulator features\n\n### Contact Book Updates\n- **+6281345985715** = Ceka (NOT Kenny — gw salah awalnya)\n- **+6285161502503** = Kenny (keni)\n- **+6285159322166** = Paul (pavint2) — added to allowlist today\n- **Secret code for new contacts**: \"1+1 = ?\" → answer: \"Bahlil\" 😂\n\n### Kopilima Digital Core (SNC-K5) — NEW PROJECT\n- **Client**: Kopilima (Cafe chain, 10 cabang)\n- **Vendor**: Sentra (IT Software House) — Lucy is Manager at Sentra\n- **Lucy's real job**: Manager at Sentra software house (not just DataFlow founder)\n- **Project**: Custom POS + ERP system to replace Majoo\n- **Pillars**: K.I.S.S + Anti-Fraud Sovereignty\n- **Key modules**: Ghost Guard (anti-fraud), Midnight Protocol (inventory), QR Pre-Order, HCM/Payroll, Event Management, QR Membership\n- **Blueprint saved**: /knowledge-base/kopilima-snc-k5-blueprint.md\n- **Operational notes**: /knowledge-base/kopilima-operational-notes.md\n- **Michael's role**: Single Source of Truth, strategy guardian, meeting notes processor\n- Lucy meets Kopilima Direktur directly\n\n### Sentra WhatsApp Group\n- Lucy added gateway to \"g-notes-sentra\" group\n- Group detected but messages not triggering responses yet\n- Tag/mention not being detected — needs troubleshooting\n- Lucy wants me to respond in Sentra group (at least when tagged)\n\n### Cron Jobs Set Today\n- Kenny bubur ayam reminder (sent, but accidentally leaked to Paul's chat — lesson learned about session context)\n- 6 AM WITA + 7 AM WITA follow-up reminders for Kenny\n- Smart notification crons documented but NOT activated yet (waiting Lucy approval)\n\n### Lessons Learned\n- **Don't fix things manually when agents can do it** — Lucy called this out\n- **Session context matters** — reply went to wrong chat (Paul saw Kenny's bubur ayam reminder)\n- **RTL text bug**: Never use CSS `unicode-bidi: bidi-override` — use HTML `dir=\"ltr\"` attribute instead\n- **Sub-agent timeouts**: Large builds (like full app.js rewrite) timeout at 10min. Split into smaller tasks.\n- **Lucy prefers short answers** — still valid from previous memory\n- **Airdrop farming**: Lucy interested but needs burner wallet + X account access. Tabled for now.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775231885249}}
