{"type":"message","id":"f0c9fc24","parentId":"6e740f84","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:25:15.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_3AU7S7sGEQoAwOnUwjQrSg","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/openclaw/dnd-app && python3 /tmp/proper_translations.py"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":73,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":97044,"totalTokens":97118,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.001825,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.606525,"total":0.608355}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775233511144}}
{"type":"message","id":"4616bf61","parentId":"f0c9fc24","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:25:15.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_3AU7S7sGEQoAwOnUwjQrSg","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written: 190 class features, 32 subclass features"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":77,"aggregated":"Written: 190 class features, 32 subclass features","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775233515806}}
{"type":"message","id":"d95f3d9c","parentId":"4616bf61","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:25:23.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — 190 class features and 32 subclass features with proper human-quality translations. Now let me add the remaining subclasses (Cleric, Druid, Fighter, Monk, Paladin, Ranger, Rogue, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard):"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_oF0e6WmWR8E6gOIbPYQmMt","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nwith open('/home/openclaw/dnd-app/data/5etools/all-classes.json') as f:\n    classes = json.load(f)\n\n# List ALL subclasses and their features\nfor c in classes:\n    for sc in c.get('subclasses', []):\n        print(f\"\\n=== {sc['name']} ({c['name']}) ===\")\n        for f in sc.get('features', []):\n            key = sc['name'].lower().replace(' ', '-').replace(\"'\", \"\") + '.' + f['name'].lower().replace(' ', '-').replace(\"'\", \"\")\n            print(f\"  [{f['level']}] {key}\")\n            print(f\"  TEXT: {f.get('entries','')[:120]}...\")\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":321,"cacheRead":97044,"cacheWrite":99,"totalTokens":97465,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.008025000000000001,"cacheRead":0.048521999999999996,"cacheWrite":0.00061875,"total":0.05717075}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775233515828}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a6fcbd1","parentId":"d95f3d9c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:25:23.583Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_oF0e6WmWR8E6gOIbPYQmMt","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Path of the Berserker (Barbarian) ===\n  [3] path-of-the-berserker.path-of-the-berserker\n  TEXT: Channel Rage into Violent Fury\n\nBarbarians who walk the Path of the Berserker direct their Rage primarily toward violenc...\n  [3] path-of-the-berserker.frenzy\n  TEXT: If you use Reckless Attack while your Rage is active, you deal extra damage to the first target you hit on your turn wit...\n  [6] path-of-the-berserker.mindless-rage\n  TEXT: You have Immunity to the Charmed and Frightened conditions while your Rage is active. If you're Charmed or Frightened wh...\n  [10] path-of-the-berserker.retaliation\n  TEXT: When you take damage from a creature that is within 5 feet of you, you can take a Reaction to make one melee attack agai...\n  [14] path-of-the-berserker.intimidating-presence\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can strike terror into others with your menacing presence and primal power. When you do so, each ...\n\n=== Path of the Wild Heart (Barbarian) ===\n  [3] path-of-the-wild-heart.path-of-the-wild-heart\n  TEXT: Walk in Community with the Animal World\n\nBarbarians who follow the Path of the Wild Heart view themselves as kin to anim...\n  [3] path-of-the-wild-heart.animal-speaker\n  TEXT: You can cast the Beast Sense and Speak with Animals spells but only as Rituals. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for ...\n  [3] path-of-the-wild-heart.rage-of-the-wilds\n  TEXT: Your Rage taps into the primal power of animals. Whenever you activate your Rage, you gain one of the following options ...\n  [6] path-of-the-wild-heart.aspect-of-the-wilds\n  TEXT: You gain one of the following options of your choice. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change your choice.\n\nOwl\n...\n  [10] path-of-the-wild-heart.nature-speaker\n  TEXT: You can cast the Commune with Nature spell but only as a Ritual. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for it....\n  [14] path-of-the-wild-heart.power-of-the-wilds\n  TEXT: Whenever you activate your Rage, you gain one of the following options of your choice.\n\nFalcon\nWhile your Rage is active...\n\n=== Path of the World Tree (Barbarian) ===\n  [3] path-of-the-world-tree.path-of-the-world-tree\n  TEXT: Trace the Roots and Branches of the Multiverse\n\nBarbarians who follow the Path of the World Tree connect with the cosmic...\n  [3] path-of-the-world-tree.vitality-of-the-tree\n  TEXT: Your Rage taps into the life force of the World Tree. You gain the following benefits.\n\nVitality Surge\nWhen you activate...\n  [6] path-of-the-world-tree.branches-of-the-tree\n  TEXT: Whenever a creature you can see starts its turn within 30 feet of you while your Rage is active, you can take a Reaction...\n  [10] path-of-the-world-tree.battering-roots\n  TEXT: During your turn, your reach is 10 feet greater with any Melee weapon that has the Heavy or Versatile property, as tendr...\n  [14] path-of-the-world-tree.travel-along-the-tree\n  TEXT: When you activate your Rage and as a Bonus Action while your Rage is active, you can teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccu...\n\n=== Path of the Zealot (Barbarian) ===\n  [3] path-of-the-zealot.path-of-the-zealot\n  TEXT: Rage in Ecstatic Union with a God\n\nBarbarians who walk the Path of the Zealot receive boons from a god or pantheon. Thes...\n  [3] path-of-the-zealot.divine-fury\n  TEXT: You can channel divine power into your strikes. On each of your turns while your Rage is active, the first creature you ...\n  [3] path-of-the-zealot.warrior-of-the-gods\n  TEXT: A divine entity helps ensure you can continue the fight. You have a pool of four d12s that you can spend to heal yoursel...\n  [6] path-of-the-zealot.fanatical-focus\n  TEXT: Once per active Rage, if you fail a saving throw, you can reroll it with a bonus equal to your Rage Damage bonus, and yo...\n  [10] path-of-the-zealot.zealous-presence\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you unleash a battle cry infused with divine energy. Up to ten other creatures of your choice within ...\n  [14] path-of-the-zealot.rage-of-the-gods\n  TEXT: When you activate your Rage, you can assume the form of a divine warrior. This form lasts for 1 minute or until you drop...\n\n=== College of Dance (Bard) ===\n  [3] college-of-dance.college-of-dance\n  TEXT: Move in Harmony with the Cosmos\n\nBards of the College of Dance know that the Words of Creation can't be contained within...\n  [3] college-of-dance.agile-strikes\n  TEXT: When you expend a use of your Bardic Inspiration as part of an action, a Bonus Action, or a Reaction, you can make one U...\n  [3] college-of-dance.bardic-damage\n  TEXT: You can use Dexterity instead of Strength for the attack rolls of your Unarmed Strikes. When you deal damage with an Una...\n  [3] college-of-dance.dance-virtuoso\n  TEXT: You have Advantage on any Charisma (Performance) check you make that involves you dancing....\n  [3] college-of-dance.dazzling-footwork\n  TEXT: While you aren't wearing armor or wielding a Shield, you gain the following benefits....\n  [3] college-of-dance.unarmored-defense\n  TEXT: Your base Armor Class equals 10 plus your Dexterity and Charisma modifiers....\n  [6] college-of-dance.inspiring-movement\n  TEXT: When an enemy you can see ends its turn within 5 feet of you, you can take a Reaction and expend one use of your Bardic ...\n  [6] college-of-dance.tandem-footwork\n  TEXT: When you roll Initiative, you can expend one use of your Bardic Inspiration if you don't have the Incapacitated conditio...\n  [14] college-of-dance.leading-evasion\n  TEXT: When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you inste...\n\n=== College of Glamour (Bard) ===\n  [3] college-of-glamour.college-of-glamour\n  TEXT: Weave Beguiling Fey Magic\n\nThe College of Glamour traces its origins to the beguiling magic of the Feywild. Bards who st...\n  [3] college-of-glamour.beguiling-magic\n  TEXT: You always have the Charm Person and Mirror Image spells prepared.\n\nIn addition, immediately after you cast an Enchantme...\n  [3] college-of-glamour.mantle-of-inspiration\n  TEXT: You can weave fey magic into a song or dance to fill others with vigor. As a Bonus Action, you can expend a use of Bardi...\n  [6] college-of-glamour.mantle-of-majesty\n  TEXT: You always have the Command spell prepared.\n\nAs a Bonus Action, you cast Command without expending a spell slot, and you...\n  [14] college-of-glamour.unbreakable-majesty\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can assume a magically majestic presence for 1 minute or until you have the Incapacitated conditi...\n\n=== College of Lore (Bard) ===\n  [3] college-of-lore.college-of-lore\n  TEXT: Plumb the Depths of Magical Knowledge\n\nBards of the College of Lore collect spells and secrets from diverse sources, suc...\n  [3] college-of-lore.bonus-proficiencies\n  TEXT: You gain proficiency with three skills of your choice....\n  [3] college-of-lore.cutting-words\n  TEXT: You learn to use your wit to supernaturally distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others...\n  [6] college-of-lore.magical-discoveries\n  TEXT: You learn two spells of your choice. These spells can come from the Cleric, Druid, or Wizard spell list or any combinati...\n  [14] college-of-lore.peerless-skill\n  TEXT: When you make an ability check or attack roll and fail, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration; roll the Bardic In...\n\n=== College of Valor (Bard) ===\n  [3] college-of-valor.college-of-valor\n  TEXT: Sing the Deeds of Ancient Heroes\n\nBards of the College of Valor are daring storytellers whose tales preserve the memory ...\n  [3] college-of-valor.combat-inspiration\n  TEXT: You can use your wit to turn the tide of battle. A creature that has a Bardic Inspiration die from you can use it for on...\n  [3] college-of-valor.martial-training\n  TEXT: You gain proficiency with Martial weapons and training with Medium armor and Shield.\n\nIn addition, you can use a Simple ...\n  [6] college-of-valor.extra-attack\n  TEXT: You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.\n\nIn addition, you can cast one of...\n  [14] college-of-valor.battle-magic\n  TEXT: After you cast a spell that has a casting time of an action, you can make one attack with a weapon as a Bonus Action....\n\n=== Life Domain (Cleric) ===\n  [3] life-domain.life-domain\n  TEXT: Soothe the Hurts of the World\n\nThe Life Domain focuses on the positive energy that helps sustain all life in the multive...\n  [3] life-domain.disciple-of-life\n  TEXT: When a spell you cast with a spell slot restores Hit Points to a creature, that creature regains additional Hit Points o...\n  [3] life-domain.life-domain-spells\n  TEXT: Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specif...\n  [3] life-domain.preserve-life\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you present your Holy Symbol and expend a use of your Channel Divinity to evoke healing energy that c...\n  [6] life-domain.blessed-healer\n  TEXT: The healing spells you cast on others heal you as well. Immediately after you cast a spell with a spell slot that restor...\n  [17] life-domain.supreme-healing\n  TEXT: When you would normally roll one or more dice to restore Hit Points to a creature with a spell or Channel Divinity, don'...\n\n=== Light Domain (Cleric) ===\n  [3] light-domain.light-domain\n  TEXT: Bring Light to Banish Darkness\n\nThe Light Domain emphasizes the divine power to bring about blazing fire and revelation....\n  [3] light-domain.light-domain-spells\n  TEXT: Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specif...\n  [3] light-domain.radiance-of-the-dawn\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you present your Holy Symbol and expend a use of your Channel Divinity to emit a flash of light in a ...\n  [3] light-domain.warding-flare\n  TEXT: When a creature that you can see within 30 feet of yourself makes an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to impose Disa...\n  [6] light-domain.improved-warding-flare\n  TEXT: You regain all expended uses of your Warding Flare when you finish a Short Rest or Long Rest.\n\nIn addition, whenever you...\n  [17] light-domain.corona-of-light\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you cause yourself to emit an aura of sunlight that lasts for 1 minute or until you dismiss it (no ac...\n\n=== Trickery Domain (Cleric) ===\n  [3] trickery-domain.trickery-domain\n  TEXT: Make Mischief and Challenge Authority\n\nThe Trickery Domain offers magic of deception, illusion, and stealth. Clerics who...\n  [3] trickery-domain.blessing-of-the-trickster\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you can choose yourself or a willing creature within 30 feet of yourself to have Advantage on Dexteri...\n  [3] trickery-domain.invoke-duplicity\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to create a perfect visual illusion of yourself in an...\n  [3] trickery-domain.trickery-domain-spells\n  TEXT: Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specif...\n  [6] trickery-domain.tricksters-transposition\n  TEXT: Whenever you take the Bonus Action to create or move the illusion of your Invoke Duplicity, you can teleport, swapping p...\n  [17] trickery-domain.improved-duplicity\n  TEXT: The illusion of your Invoke Duplicity has grown more powerful in the following ways.\n\nShared Distraction\nWhen you and yo...\n\n=== War Domain (Cleric) ===\n  [3] war-domain.war-domain\n  TEXT: Inspire Valor and Smite Foes\n\nWar has many manifestations. It can make heroes of ordinary people. It can be desperate an...\n  [3] war-domain.guided-strike\n  TEXT: When you or a creature within 30 feet of you misses with an attack roll, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity...\n  [3] war-domain.war-domain-spells\n  TEXT: Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specif...\n  [3] war-domain.war-priest\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can make one attack with a weapon or an Unarmed Strike. You can use this Bonus Action a number of...\n  [6] war-domain.war-gods-blessing\n  TEXT: You can expend a use of your Channel Divinity to cast Shield of Faith or Spiritual Weapon rather than expending a spell ...\n  [17] war-domain.avatar-of-battle\n  TEXT: You gain Resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage....\n\n=== Circle of the Land (Druid) ===\n  [3] circle-of-the-land.circle-of-the-land\n  TEXT: Celebrate Connection to the Natural World\n\nThe Circle of the Land comprises mystics and sages who safeguard ancient know...\n  [3] circle-of-the-land.circle-of-the-land-spells\n  TEXT: Whenever you finish a Long Rest, choose one type of land: arid, polar, temperate, or tropical. Consult the table below t...\n  [3] circle-of-the-land.lands-aid\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape and choose a point within 60 feet of yourself. Vitality-givin...\n  [6] circle-of-the-land.natural-recovery\n  TEXT: You can cast one of the level 1+ spells that you have prepared from your Circle Spells feature without expending a spell...\n  [10] circle-of-the-land.natures-ward\n  TEXT: You are immune to the Poisoned condition, and you have Resistance to a damage type associated with your current land cho...\n  [14] circle-of-the-land.natures-sanctuary\n  TEXT: As a Magic action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape and cause spectral trees and vines to appear in a 15-foot Cub...\n\n=== Circle of the Moon (Druid) ===\n  [3] circle-of-the-moon.circle-forms\n  TEXT: You can channel lunar magic when you assume a Wild Shape form, granting you the benefits below.\n\nChallenge Rating\nThe ma...\n  [3] circle-of-the-moon.circle-of-the-moon\n  TEXT: Adopt Animal Forms to Guard the Wilds\n\nDruids of the Circle of the Moon draw on lunar magic to transform themselves. The...\n  [3] circle-of-the-moon.circle-of-the-moon-spells\n  TEXT: When you reach a Druid level specified in the Circle of the Moon Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spe...\n  [6] circle-of-the-moon.improved-circle-forms\n  TEXT: While in a Wild Shape form, you gain the following benefits.\n\nLunar Radiance\nEach of your attacks in a Wild Shape form c...\n  [10] circle-of-the-moon.moonlight-step\n  TEXT: You magically transport yourself, reappearing amid a burst of moonlight. As a Bonus Action, you teleport up to 30 feet t...\n  [14] circle-of-the-moon.lunar-form\n  TEXT: The power of the moon suffuses you, granting you the following benefits.\n\nImproved Lunar Radiance\nOnce per turn, you can...\n\n=== Circle of the Sea (Druid) ===\n  [3] circle-of-the-sea.circle-of-the-sea\n  TEXT: Become One with Tides and Storms\n\nDruids of the Circle of the Sea draw on the tempestuous forces of oceans and storms. S...\n  [3] circle-of-the-sea.circle-of-the-sea-spells\n  TEXT: When you reach a Druid level specified in the Circle of the Sea Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spel...\n  [3] circle-of-the-sea.wrath-of-the-sea\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape to manifest a 5-foot Emanation [Area of Effect] that takes th...\n  [6] circle-of-the-sea.aquatic-affinity\n  TEXT: The size of the Emanation [Area of Effect] created by your Wrath of the Sea increases to 10 feet.\n\nIn addition, you gain...\n  [10] circle-of-the-sea.stormborn\n  TEXT: Your Wrath of the Sea confers two more benefits while active, as detailed below.\n\nFlight\nYou gain a Fly Speed equal to y...\n  [14] circle-of-the-sea.oceanic-gift\n  TEXT: Instead of manifesting the Emanation [Area of Effect] of Wrath of the Sea around yourself, you can manifest it around on...\n\n=== Circle of the Stars (Druid) ===\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.circle-of-the-stars\n  TEXT: Harness Secrets Hidden in Constellations\n\nThe Circle of the Stars has tracked heavenly patterns since time immemorial, d...\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.star-map\n  TEXT: You've created a star chart as part of your heavenly studies. It is a Tiny object, and you can use it as a Spellcasting ...\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.starry-form\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape feature to take on a starry form rather than shape-shifting.\n...\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.archer\n  TEXT: A constellation of an archer appears on you. When you activate this form and as a Bonus Action on your subsequent turns ...\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.chalice\n  TEXT: A constellation of a life-giving goblet appears on you. Whenever you cast a spell using a spell slot that restores Hit P...\n  [3] circle-of-the-stars.dragon\n  TEXT: A constellation of a wise dragon appears on you. When you make an Intelligence or a Wisdom check or a Constitution savin...\n  [6] circle-of-the-stars.cosmic-omen\n  TEXT: Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can consult your Star Map for omens and roll a die. Until you finish your next Long...\n  [10] circle-of-the-stars.twinkling-constellations\n  TEXT: The constellations of your Starry Form improve. The 1d8 of the Archer and the Chalice becomes 2d8, and while the Dragon ...\n  [14] circle-of-the-stars.full-of-stars\n  TEXT: While in your Starry Form, you become partially incorporeal, giving you Resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashin...\n\n=== Battle Master (Fighter) ===\n  [3] battle-master.battle-master\n  TEXT: Master Sophisticated Battle Maneuvers\n\nBattle Masters are students of the art of battle, learning martial techniques pas...\n  [3] battle-master.combat-superiority\n  TEXT: Your experience on the battlefield has refined your fighting techniques. You learn maneuvers that are fueled by special ...\n  [3] battle-master.maneuver-options\n  TEXT: The maneuvers are presented here in alphabetical order....\n  [3] battle-master.student-of-war\n  TEXT: You gain proficiency with one type of Artisan's Tools of your choice, and you gain proficiency in one skill of your choi...\n  [7] battle-master.know-your-enemy\n  TEXT: As a Bonus Action, you can discern certain strengths and weaknesses of a creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself...\n  [10] battle-master.improved-combat-superiority\n  TEXT: Your Superiority Die becomes a d10....\n  [15] battle-master.relentless\n  TEXT: Once per turn, when you use a maneuver, you can roll 1d8 and use the number rolled instead of expending a Superiority Di...\n  [18] battle-master.ultimate-combat-superiority\n  TEXT: Your Superiority Die becomes a d12....\n\n=== Champion (Fighter) ===\n  [3] champion.champion\n  TEXT: Pursue Physical Excellence in Combat\n\nA Champion focuses on the development of martial prowess in a relentless pursuit o...\n  [3] champion.improved-critical\n  TEXT: Your attack rolls with weapons and Unarmed Strikes can score a Critical Hit on a roll of 19 or 20 on the d20....\n  [3] champion.remarkable-athlete\n  TEXT: Thanks to your athleticism, you have Advantage on Initiative rolls and Strength (Athletics) checks.\n\nIn addition, immedi...\n  [7] champion.additional-fighting-style\n  TEXT: You gain another Fighting Style feat of your choice....\n  [10] champion.heroic-warrior\n  TEXT: The thrill of battle drives you toward victory. During combat, you can give yourself Heroic Inspiration whenever you sta...\n  [15] champion.superior-critical\n  TEXT: Your attack rolls with weapons and Unarmed Strikes can now score a Critical Hit on a roll of 18–20 on the d20....\n  [18] champion.survivor\n  TEXT: You attain the pinnacle of resilience in battle, giving you these benefits.\n\nDefy Death\nYou have Advantage on Death Savi...\n\n=== Eldritch Knight (Fighter) ===\n  [3] eldritch-knight.eldritch-knight\n  TEXT: Support Combat S