{"type":"message","id":"9e7d90ca","parentId":"ba3af46c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:41:28.434Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_h1a20u4eAK0vqMNCgQVnqL","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Best LLM for Coding (March 2026): GPT-5.4 vs Claude 4.6 vs GLM-5 ...\nURL: https://docs.kanaries.net/articles/best-llm-for-coding\nIf your main priority is daily coding cost efficiency, Claude Sonnet 4.6 is the safer pick. Is GPT-5.4 better than GPT-5.3-Codex for coding?\n\n## I Tested 15 LLMs: Claude, GPT, Gemini on 38 Tasks - Ian L. Paterson\nURL: https://ianlpaterson.com/blog/llm-benchmark-2026-38-actual-tasks-15-models-for-2-29/\n[Skip to content](https://ianlpaterson.com/blog/llm-benchmark-2026-38-actual-tasks-15-models-for-2-29/#main). *   [The Problem I Was Solving](https://ianlpaterson.com/blog/llm-benchmark-2026-38-actual-tasks-15-models-for-2-29/#the-problem-i-was-solving). *   [Key Findings](https://ianlpaterson.com/b\n\n## LLM Coding Benchmark Showdown 2026: Claude | ToLearn Blog\nURL: https://tolearn.blog/blog/llm-coding-benchmark-comparison-2026\nReal benchmark data from SWE-bench, LiveCodeBench, and developer testing reveals which AI codes best. | Benchmark | What It Tests | Why It Matters | |-----------|---------------|----------------| | **SWE-bench Verified** | Real GitHub bug fixes | Gold standard for production coding | | **LiveCodeBen\n\n## Which LLM Should You Use for Coding? (Feb 2026, data-driven)\nURL: https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/which-llm-should-you-use-coding-feb-2026-data-driven-dipesh-sukhani-ws2zf\nThe short list of leading coding models · Anthropic: Claude Opus 4.6 (high-stakes reasoning + debugging), Claude Sonnet 4.5 (balanced workhorse).\n\n## Best LLM for Coding (2026) — AI Model Rankings | Price Per Token\nURL: https://pricepertoken.com/leaderboards/coding\nGet real-time LLM pricing in Claude Code and Cursor. Price Per TokenPrice Per Token. # Best LLM for Coding. Compare coding performance across LLMs ran